annotation: Looks like a loan from an Oceanic language
PAN quluh (includes Seediq qolux 'skull', Saisiat ta?ölöh head'

language: East Sumbanese, Umbu Ratu Nggai dialect
Kadazan Dusun of Taginambur, Kota Belud, Sabah, Malaysia

annotation: Interdental lateral approximant with tongue lengthening diacritic.
1. Head of a person or animal
head; irregular insertion of glottal between two vowels
wil is the 3SG form; the inflecting root for other person-numbers is ulu-; also wil tabi in 3SG, where tabi is a shape classifier.
